' ============================== enums ========================================
enum UserStatus <<native PG enum user_status>> {
  EMAIL_VERIFY_PENDING
  ACTIVE
  SUSPENDED
  BANNED
  DELETION_PENDING
  DELETED
}

enum AvatarSource {
  Default = 0
  Uploaded = 1
  Google = 2
  GitHub = 3
  GitLab = 4
}

enum SalaryPeriod {
  Monthly = 1
  Yearly = 2
}

enum AutoCloseRule {
  None = 0
  CloseOnEndDate = 1
  CloseOnHiringTarget = 2
  Either = 3
}

enum OrganizationRole <<code vocabulary only>> {
  OWNER
  REPRESENTATIVE
  HR
  MEMBER
}

note bottom of OrganizationRole
  ⚠ GROUND-TRUTH §2: NO entity property is typed as this enum.
  OrganizationMembership.Role, OrganizationAuthority.Role and
  WorkspaceMember.Role are plain `string`.
  ⚠ "Recruiter" is not a role in this system.
end note

note bottom of UserStatus
  The only native PostgreSQL enum in the schema (§4).
  All other enums are stored as integer or text.
end note

